SUMMARY:Your DC Moment | Dinner with Ambassador and Professor Lee Feinstein
DESCRIPTION:Stop studying global leadership and start practicing it. Join
  Ambassador and Professor Lee Feinstein\, our D.C. Program Academic Direc
 tor\, for an exclusive working dinner and strategy session for the Spring
  2027 D.C. Global Policy Program.  This intimate dinner is for students i
 nterested in the Hamilton Lugar Spring 2027 residency. It's a working din
 ner and a peek at what a global career actually feels like before you ste
 p into it.Why you should attend:Sit at the Table: Engage with leaders who
  have shaped global policy and international careers.    Alumni Insights:
  Hear from a panel of D.C. Program alumni regarding their on-the-ground e
 xperiences.    Professional Roadmap: Get a technical walkthrough of the S
 pring 2027 cycle\, including the January 12 – May 2 residency dates.   
  The Logistics Bridge: Understand how the IU Capital Campus housing works
  and how the classes work for undergrads\, grad\, and PhD students.    Th
 e Strategy Session AgendaI. The Practitioner Perspective: A briefing from
  Ambassador Lee Feinstein on D.C. professional realities and "tradecraft"
  skills.    II. The Roadmap: A deep dive into the October 15 deadline\, i
 nterview sprints (Oct 26–28)\, and the mandatory December 12 orientatio
 n.    III. Housing &amp\; Classes: Guidance on the Capital Campus residen
 cy and the academic courses offered in D.C.    IV. Ground Game: Peer-to-p
 eer breakouts and alumni panel discussion on commuting\, and professional
  life in DC.    Biography: Ambassador &amp\; Professor Lee Feinstein  Amb
 assador Lee Feinstein is a Senior Managing Director and the President of 
 McLarty Associates. He previously served as the U.S. Ambassador to the Re
 public of Poland and held senior positions at the Department of State\, i
 ncluding Principal Deputy Director and a Member of the Policy Planning St
 aff. He was the Founding Dean of the Hamilton Lugar School of Global and 
 International Studies at Indiana University from 2014 to 2022. Ambassador
  Feinstein is a member of the Council on Foreign Relations and the Americ
 an Academy of Diplomacy\, and holds a JD from Georgetown University Law C
 enter.  &#160\;Can't make the full hour? No problem. This is a come-and-g
 o strategy session designed to fit your Thursday schedule.
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<p data-path-to-node="5">  Stop studying glo
 bal leadership and start practicing it. Join Ambassador and Professor Lee
  Feinstein\, our D.C. Program Academic Director\, for an exclusive workin
 g dinner and strategy session for the Spring 2027 D.C. Global Policy Prog
 ram.</p><p data-path-to-node="5">  This intimate dinner is for students i
 nterested in the Hamilton Lugar Spring 2027 residency. It's a working din
 ner and a peek at what a global career actually feels like before you ste
 p into it.</p><p data-path-to-node="7"><strong data-path-to-node="7" data
