 es.    </p></li><li><p data-path-to-node="8\,3\,0"><strong data-path-to-n
 ode="8\,3\,0" data-index-in-node="0">The Logistics Bridge:</strong> Under
 stand how the <strong data-path-to-node="8\,3\,0" data-index-in-node="41"
 >IU Capital Campus</strong> housing works and how the classes work for un
 dergrads\, grad\, and PhD students.    </p></li></ul><h3 data-path-to-nod
 e="10"><strong data-path-to-node="10" data-index-in-node="0">The Strategy
  Session Agenda</strong></h3><ul data-path-to-node="11"><li><p data-path-
 to-node="11\,0\,0"><strong data-path-to-node="11\,0\,0" data-index-in-nod
 e="0">I. The Practitioner Perspective:</strong> A briefing from Ambassado
 r Lee Feinstein on D.C. professional realities and "tradecraft" skills.  
   </p></li><li><p data-path-to-node="11\,1\,0"><strong data-path-to-node=
 "11\,1\,0" data-index-in-node="0">II. The Roadmap:</strong> A deep dive i
 nto the <strong data-path-to-node="11\,1\,0" data-index-in-node="38">Octo
 ber 15</strong> deadline\, interview sprints (Oct 26–28)\, and the mand
 atory December 12 orientation.    </p></li><li><p data-path-to-node="11\,
 2\,0"><strong data-path-to-node="11\,2\,0" data-index-in-node="0">III. Ho
 using &amp\; Classes:</strong> Guidance on the Capital Campus residency a
 nd the academic courses offered in D.C.    </p></li><li><p data-path-to-n
