DTSTART:20261012T160000Z
DTEND:20261012T173000Z
SUMMARY:The Cyber-Policy Nexus: HLS Global Policy Program Briefing for Cy
 bersecurity and Global Policy Students
DESCRIPTION:n Washington\, D.C.\, policy is the new perimeter. Join Isak 
 Nti-Asare (Co-Director\, Cybersecurity and Global Policy Program) and Kat
 herine Ntiamoah (Director of Policy Engagement) for a targeted "come and 
 go" lunch regarding the Spring 2027 D.C. Global Policy Program.  This ses
 sion is designed specifically for students in the Cybersecurity and Globa
 l Policy joint degree. Whether your goal is a residency at CISA\, the Dep
 artment of Justice\, the NSA\, or a private sector tech policy firm\, thi
 s is your chance to see how the D.C. residency functions as a professiona
 l launchpad for your technical expertise.What to Expect:The Cyber Pipelin
 e: Guidance on identifying and securing D.C. internship placements that v
 alue the Luddy/HLS joint-degree background.    Day 1 Readiness: How our "
 tradecraft" model prepares you to brief officials on complex cyber threat
 s from your first day in the capital.    The Roadmap: A technical walkthr
 ough of the October 15 application deadline and the January 12 start date
  for the Spring residency.    Open House Format: We know your schedule is
  tight. Drop in for 20 minutes to grab lunch and the HLS D.C. Guide\, or 
 stay for the full discussion.
