SUMMARY:2026 Conference on Global Indigenous Studies (CGIS)
DESCRIPTION:CGIS 2026 is a transdisciplinary event that will bring togeth
 er national and international scholars\, educators\, practitioners\, stud
 ents\, policy makers\, activists\, academic institutions\, Indigenous org
 anizations\, grassroots organizations\, governmental and non-governmental
  organizations. The participants in this conference will be involved in a
  local and global dialogue and exchange of ideas\, research\, and experie
 nces on the themes of the event.  Across the globe\, ethnic minorities an
 d Indigenous communities have consistently strived to protect their rich 
 cultural heritages and linguistic nuances from the influences of colonial
  powers\, expanding nation-states\, and the homogenizing impact of global
 ization. This collective effort is increasingly recognized\, highlighted 
 by the initiation of UNESCO's "Indigenous Languages Decade" (2022-2032) (
 https://www.unesco.org/en/decades/indigenous-languages/community/adhocgro
 ups). The imperative acknowledgment is that Indigenous languages\, along 
 with the intricate knowledge systems interwoven within them\, stand as cr
 ucial pillars for preserving both biological and cultural pluralism.Propo
 sal Submission (https://app.oxfordabstracts.com/auth?redirect=/stages/800
 09/submitter) Deadline: April 30\, 2026Registration Costs (https://indian
 auniv.ungerboeck.com/prod/emc00/register.aspx?aat=2f74415350355073564f6a6
 a762f4163555748484461566c746378794d6f4d4d67444739715679693634733d)  Early
  Bird Registration: $60.00 (Before October 1\, 2026)  Standard Registrati
 on: $80.00 (October 1 - November 15\, 2026)  &#160\;2026 Keynote Speakers
 :  Aluki Kotierk  Armando Muyolema  Diego A. Titueña Matango  Teresa L. 
 McCarty  &#160\;  Conference on Global and Indigenous Studies (CGIS) is m
 ade possible by the support from:&#160\;African Studies Program (https://
 africanstudies.indiana.edu/index.html?_gl=1*4pv3u5*_gcl_au*MTI2NDk4MTcxLj
 E3NzUwNTYwNjQ.*_ga*MTUxNzYzNjMwOS4xNzc1MDU2MDUw*_ga_61CH0D2DQW*czE3NzY5Nj
 g4MDEkbzMzJGcwJHQxNzc2OTY4ODAxJGo2MCRsMCRoMA..)Arts and Humanities Future
 s – Indigenous Futures at IUB (https://ahfutures.iu.edu/)Center for Lat
 in American and Caribbean Studies (https://clacs.indiana.edu/index.html)C
 enter for the Study of Global Change (https://global.indiana.edu/index.ht
 ml)Center for the Study of the Middle East (https://csme.indiana.edu/inde
 x.html)East Asian Studies Center (https://easc.indiana.edu/index.html)Inn
 er Asian and Uralic National Resource Center (https://iaunrc.indiana.edu/
